<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Saurma</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial German Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July 27,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: Adverting to the note
                            of the 16th ultimo from Mr. Uhl, Acting Secretary of State, concerning
                            the increase in salary of Chief Justice Ide in Samoa, I have the honor
                            to inform your excellency that the imperial consulate at Apia has been
                            instructed to pay to Mr. Ide $333.33⅓, the Imperial Government’s share
                            of the additional traveling expenses of $1,000 which has been allowed
                            him.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Saurma.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>